61 template <typename T, typename Container>
62 class RangeIterator {
63  public:
64  typedef RangeIterator<T, Container> RangeIterator_;
65 
66  // Standard iterator typedefs
67  typedef std::vector<T> value_type;
68  typedef const value_type& reference;
69  typedef const value_type* pointer;
70  typedef std::input_iterator_tag iterator_category;
71  typedef std::ptrdiff_t difference_type;
72 
74 
76  RangeIterator(const RangeIterator_& other)
77  : container_(other.container_), current_(other.current_) {}
78 
80 
83  RangeIterator(const T* v, const Container* c)
84  : container_(c), current_(v, v + c->rank()) {}
85 
87 
90  RangeIterator_& operator=(const RangeIterator_& other) {
91  current_ = other.current_;
92  container_ = other.container_;
93 
94  return *this;
95  }
96 
97  const Container* container() const { return container_; }
98 
100 
103  reference operator*() const {
104  TA_ASSERT(container_->includes(current_));
105  return current_;
106  }
107 
109 
112  RangeIterator_& operator++() {
113  TA_ASSERT(container_->includes(current_));
114  container_->increment(current_);
115  return *this;
116  }
117 
119 
122  RangeIterator_ operator++(int) {
123  TA_ASSERT(container_->includes(current_));
124  RangeIterator_ temp(*this);
125  container_->increment(current_);
126  return temp;
127  }
128 
130 
132  pointer operator->() const {
133  TA_ASSERT(container_->includes(current_));
134  return &current_;
135  }
136 
137  void advance(difference_type n) {
138  TA_ASSERT(container_->includes(current_));
139  container_->advance(current_, n);
140  }
141 
142  difference_type distance_to(const RangeIterator_& other) const {
143  TA_ASSERT(container_ == other.container_);
144  TA_ASSERT(container_->includes(current_));
145  return container_->distance_to(current_, other.current_);
146  }
147 
148  private:
149  const Container* container_;
150  std::vector<T> current_;
151 
152  template <typename U, typename C>
153  friend bool operator==(const RangeIterator<U, C>& left_it,
154  const RangeIterator<U, C>& right_it);
155 
159  reference value() const { return current_; }
160 
161 }; // class RangeIterator

173 template <typename T, typename Container>
174 bool operator==(const RangeIterator<T, Container>& left_it,
175  const RangeIterator<T, Container>& right_it) {
176  return (left_it.value() == right_it.value()) &&
177  (left_it.container() == right_it.container());
178 }
179 
181 
189 template <typename T, typename Container>
190 bool operator!=(const RangeIterator<T, Container>& left_it,
191  const RangeIterator<T, Container>& right_it) {
192  // return (left_it.value() != right_it.value()) ||
193  // (left_it.container() != right_it.container());
194  return !(left_it == right_it);
195 }

209 template <typename T, typename Container>
210 typename TiledArray::detail::RangeIterator<T, Container>::difference_type
211 distance(const TiledArray::detail::RangeIterator<T, Container>& first,
212  const TiledArray::detail::RangeIterator<T, Container>& last) {
